<subSubSection pageId="187" pageNumber="466" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="187.[740,1333,2500,2922]" lastBlockId="187.[127,1332,2933,3476]" pageId="187" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[741,1020,2771,2804]" pageId="187" pageNumber="466">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 117-133 mm, tail 79-96 mm, hindfoot 23— 27 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. See general characters of the genus under the Amazonian Hocicudo (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hershkovitz" authorityYear="1994" box="[758,950,2933,2962]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Oxymycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="187" pageNumber="466" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amazonicus">O. amazonicus</taxonomicName>
) account. The Elfin Forest Hocicudo is a medium-sized species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1837" box="[692,849,2973,3002]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Oxymycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="187" pageNumber="466" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oxymycterus</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is light brownish; venter is yellowish wash but with dark gray bases of hairs apparent. Hairs of forefeet and hindfeet are almost totally unpigmented;tail is dark above and nonpigmented or light brownish below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="187" pageNumber="466" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="187.[127,1332,2933,3476]" pageId="187" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[128,239,3126,3159]" pageId="187" pageNumber="466">Habitat.</emphasis>
Cold temperate forests, second growth brush, and fields in valleys edged by abruptcliffs with 
<taxonomicName box="[374,445,3165,3198]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Puna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="187" pageNumber="466" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Puna</taxonomicName>
vegetation at elevations of 2000-3350 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
